        <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>

            <p>Bernofsky has an MFA in fiction writing from Washington University in St. Louis and a
                PhD in Comparative Literature from Princeton University. She has translated
                contemporary and classical fiction by Ludwig Harig, Herman Hesse and Robert Walser
                and was the recipient of the 2006 Helen and Kurt Wolff Translator's Prize for
                Outstanding Translation from German into English for her translation of Jenny
                Erpenbeck's <title render="italic">The Old Child and Other Stories.</title></p>

        </bioghist>
        
